Robert Durst was indicted Wednesday on the two weapons charges that have kept him in New Orleans . 
 Grand jury charged Durst with possession of a firearm by a felon, and possession of both a firearm and an illegal drug: 5 ounces of marijuana . 
 On Thursday he appeared in court to plead not guilty . 
 Durst, 71, is wanted in California for the murder of his friend Susan Berman . 
 Berman, an author who formerly acted a media spokeswoman for Durst, was shot in the head at her Benedict Canyon home in 2000 . 
 